# plot the '(%) Unemployed (excluding full-time students) - Ethnic group: Non White' on a map

column_to_plot = 'Age 16 to 49 -(%) Unemployed (excluding full-time students) - Ethnic group: Non White'

# spatial plot
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(10, 8))
unem_greater_man_geo.plot(
    column=column_to_plot,
    ax=ax,
    legend=True,
    cmap='OrRd',
    edgecolor='black',
    linewidth=0.5
)

ax.set_title('Unemployed Population (%) (Non White, Age 1649, excluding students)', fontsize=14)
ax.axis('off')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In[55]:
# define the column to plot for unemployment
column_to_plot = 'Age 16 to 49 -(%) Unemployed (excluding full-time students) - Ethnic group: Non White'

# create a figure with 1 row and 2 columns
fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(20, 10))

# Plot 1: Green spaces in Greater Manchester
greater_man_geo.plot(ax=ax1, color='lightgrey', edgecolor='black')
gs_in_greater_man_boun = gs_in_greater_man
gs_in_greater_man_boun.plot(ax=ax1, color='green', markersize=0.5, label='Green Spaces')
ax1.set_title("Green Spaces within Greater Manchester", fontsize=14)
ax1.set_xlabel("Longitude")
ax1.set_ylabel("Latitude")
ax1.legend()

# Plot 2: Unemployment among Non-White population
unem_greater_man_geo.plot(
    column=column_to_plot,
    ax=ax2,
    legend=True,
    cmap='OrRd',
    edgecolor='black',
    linewidth=0.5
)
ax2.set_title('Unemployed Population (%)\n(Non White, Age 1649, excluding students)', fontsize=14)
ax2.axis('off')

# show the plot
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

The analysis of green spaces and non-white unemployment rates in Greater Manchester shows a slight link between higher unemployment and lower green space density in very few areas (centre, north east). However, the overall distribution of green spaces is fairly even across the region, suggesting that any environmental justice issues are not widespread.

Using hotspot analysis with Getis-Ord Gi* statistics would reveal significant green space clusters, while converting data to accessibility metrics and performing correlation analysis would provide a more objective comparison.
